<br>
In particular, given that these new pets use malachite, epic mages who hadn't thought of going for elemental pact might do so. At least, I think that my new strategy may be to go for ele pact.<br>
<br>
Mind you, I already have RS3, Regen3, SCM3, SCF3, MC1, QS2, IR so I have the &quot;big ones&quot; out of the way (except QS3 but I'm going to hit a few other AAs before I do that as it's not THAT large a difference from QS2 + focus).<br>
<br>
I'm leaning towards going for Elemental Pact so I have some easier chaining opportunities with new pets (assuming they are better than epic) as well as some decent mana regen opportunities.<br>
<br>
After that, I'm probably going to go for mend companion. Yes, it's rarely used/needed but the times when my cleric doesn't get to heal my pet in time (or is otherwise occupied) is frequent enough to warrant it, especially given how often I actually pull for our raids and I use my pet as a refreshable 4K hp rune.<br>
<br>
Next up I'm torn  between getting pet discipline so I can more easily use pets in areas where we're dealing with AE mobs (TOV primarily but who knows what POP will have in store) and Frenzied Burnout for whenever it actually becomes useful. I envision FB being particularly important for PVP (yes, I'm on a pvp server).<br>
<br>
